					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'm currently in the early stages of programming an NFL football game. I plan to make a better version of Tecmo Super Bowl that modernizes the game and includes better graphics, gameplay, and options. As it stands, I am using MMC3 mapper 004. I am looking for the best mapper for this project, preferably one that incorporates CHR RAM which I have never used before. I see that TQROM mapper 119 has both CHR ROM and CHR RAM but only 128 PRG and 64 CHR. This will not be enough. I will need something close to 128 KiB for field graphics alone. I want CHR RAM so I can animate players more smoothly and create pixel-by-pixel tile effects on objects like the flags that hang on the goal posts.<br /><br />What mapper would you suggest? Should I consider MMC5 or MMC6?</div>

					
						<br clear="all" /><br />

