				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">There are a bunch of pirate knockoffs of MMC3 with CHR-RAM and CHR-ROM, supporting 2KiB to 4 KiB CHR RAM and 128 to 254 KiB CHR ROM. (Mappers 74, 191, 192, 194, 195)<br /><br />For manufacturability, I think the best option is to just use a large CHR-RAM (128KiB ones are easily purchased currently) and upload all the graphic data from PRG-ROM instead.<br /><br />Note that if emulator compatibility is an objective, that will preclude anything not explicitly in <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/MMC3_with_CHR_ROM_and_CHR_RAM" class="postlink">this list</a>.</div>

