						<div class="postbody">If you're not going to use scanline IRQs, even the MMC3 is probably overkill. Which of the MMC3's features are you planning on using, and for what purposes?<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">raydempsey wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I will need something close to 128 KiB for field graphics alone.</div><br />Why do you need over 8,000 tiles to draw football fields? I also don't see why you'd need CHR-ROM + CHR-RAM. Isn't it just a football field (which I can't imagine using more than 256 tiles) with a few animated tiles, plus the animated players as sprites?</div>

